Development continued with the goal of using the video stream published by the 
ESP32-CAM within the Python application. Initially, the MJPEG streaming format 
used by the ESP32-CAM was studied, and different methods for processing this 
type of stream in Python were investigated.

Using the requests library, a connection was established to the HTTP video stream g
enerated by the ESP32-CAM. The incoming data packets were analyzed, and methods for 
extracting individual JPEG frames from the MJPEG stream were implemented. The 
extracted frames were reconstructed with OpenCV and displayed successfully on the 
screen.

During this stage, several issues were encountered, including intermittent connection 
losses, incomplete data packets, and occasional freezing of the video stream. Different 
camera resolutions, connection parameters, and network configurations were tested to 
determine the causes of these problems. By the end of the day, the ESP32-CAM video stream 
had been successfully transferred to the Python environment with satisfactory performance.
